cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on facial landmark estimation, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a novel approach using a classifier. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of uncertainty estimates and top-down context, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions video streams, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia), and interactive human users, which relates to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
